1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Hi and welcome to this introduction to WordPress.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
In this lesson, we'll delve into the basics,

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,000
helping you gain a fundamental understanding of what you can achieve with WordPress, even if you're a complete beginner.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
The learning outcomes for this session are to define WordPress,

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
discuss what can be achieved using WordPress,

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000
explore examples of WordPress sites, clarify what open source means,

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
and briefly discuss the importance of themes and plugins.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Add its core, WordPress empowers you to create your own website,

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
or blog.

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Millions and millions of websites have been built using WordPress,

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:46,000
ranging from online stores and small businesses to renowned entities like NASA, the Walt Disney Company,

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
and the Facebook Newsroom.

13
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
But first things first, WordPress is a CMS or content management system.

14
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
In simple terms, it is a free tool or platform that helps you create, edit, and manage your own website or blog without needing to learn code.

15
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Whether you're a small business owner, a passionate blogger, or an aspiring entrepreneur,

16
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
WordPress provides the perfect platform to showcase your ideas, products, and services to the world.

17
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Did you know more than 40% of all the websites in the world are built using WordPress?

18
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
You can therefore rest assured that it is an extremely reliable, secure, and sustainable platform to use.

19
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Let's look at a few examples to see what type of websites have been built on WordPress.

20
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
First up, we have the Art Gallery of Ballarat, which is a gallery situated in Australia.

21
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
They have an extensive collection of artwork, host exhibitions, and also sell jewelry gifts and accessories.

22
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
The next example is a business website of a plumbing company based in Cape Town.

23
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
And as you will notice, the homepage is full of helpful information.

24
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
We can read about the services, see testimonials, and also find out where they are situated and how we can contact them.

25
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
The third example is of a food blog named Minimalist Baker, where you can find simple recipes, shop for kitchen utensils,

26
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
and also learn more about baking and cooking.

27
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
The last example is of a website named Mrs. O. Around the World.

28
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
It is a luxury travel blog, filled with travel hacks, guides, and more.

29
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Something else to mention is that WordPress is open source.

30
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
That means it is a free software that anyone can download and use.

31
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
It also means that anyone can contribute to the code or in other areas of WordPress to help improve it.

32
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Even you can get involved.

33
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
There are two important elements to remember when you start building your WordPress site, themes, and plugins.

34
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
You will need a theme that will determine the look and feel of your website.

35
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
And there are thousands of free and premium themes to choose from.

36
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
And secondly, WordPress allows you to install plugins to add extra functionality to your website.

37
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Plugins can, for example, be added if you want to sell products on your site, to improve the security or speed of your website, to add forms, etc.

38
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
And please note, the themes and plugins featured here are merely examples.

39
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
So to summarize, WordPress is a free tool you can use to build a website without knowing any code.

40
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,000
WordPress is used by individuals such as bloggers, small business owners, etc.

41
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,000
as well as large companies and even government agencies.

42
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
WordPress is truly for everyone.

43
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
But now you might be asking what happens after our download WordPress?

44
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
That is a great question and exactly what we will be talking about in our next video, as you will need a domain name and a place to host your site.

45
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
All the best as you start your journey with WordPress.

